# RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)

## Context
The RAG system embeds document chunks via OpenAI, stores them in pgvector, retrieves by cosine similarity, and generates answers with an LLM. Core files: `app/services/search.py` (enhanced search with enrichment boosts), `app/services/embeddings.py` (OpenAI, Cohere rerank), `routes.py` (API), `models.py`, `schemas.py`. The web/API query and search endpoints use `enhanced_search`; the CLI chat (`app/cli/chat.py`) uses raw vector+rerank.

## Embedding
- Model: `text-embedding-3-small` (1536 dimensions)
- Batch API: `get_embeddings(texts: list[str])` for bulk, `get_embedding(text: str)` for single
- Stored in `chunks.embedding` column (`Vector(1536)` via pgvector)

## Vector Search
- Operator: `<=>` (cosine distance) — lower = more similar
- Score displayed as `1 - distance` (higher = better)
- Always use `ORDER BY embedding <=> :embedding LIMIT :limit`
- Embedding param must be passed as `str(embedding)` for pgvector text format

### Search query pattern
```sql
SELECT c.content, c.page_number, c.chunk_index,
       d.filename,
       c.embedding <=> :embedding AS distance
FROM chunks c
JOIN documents d ON d.id = c.document_id
ORDER BY c.embedding <=> :embedding
LIMIT :limit
```

## Reranking
- **Cohere** reranker applied after vector search, before returning results
- Model: `rerank-v3.5` (configurable via `settings.rerank_model`)
- Over-fetch: `top_k * settings.rerank_top_n_multiplier` (default 4x), then rerank down to `top_k`
- Function: `rerank(query, documents, top_n)` in `app/services/embeddings.py`
- Each dict must have a `"content"` key; returned list preserves other fields, score replaced by Cohere relevance
- Applied in `app/services/search.py` (enhanced_search), routes tool execution, and `app/cli/chat.py`

## Enhanced Search (`app/services/search.py`)
- Uses `enhanced_search(query, db, top_k)` for API/query endpoints
- When enrichment data exists: LLM expands query into 8 signal types (context_cues, fact_cues, description_cues, tag_cues + regex variants), applies embedding and regex boosts against `memories` and `document_enrichments`, then Cohere rerank
- Falls back to plain vector+rerank when no enrichment data
- Returns `EnhancedSearchResponse` with `user_query`, `generated_cues`, `generated_regexes`, `results` (list of `DocumentResult`)

## LLM Answer Generation
- Model: `gpt-4o-mini`
- System prompt instructs to only use provided context
- Context: top-K chunks joined with `---` separators
- Used in API (`ask_llm`) and CLI chatbot (tool calling)

## Database Models

### Document
| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| id | UUID | PK, auto-generated |
| filename | VARCHAR | Original PDF name |
| path | VARCHAR | Nullable; filesystem path (batch ingest only), unique |
| page_count | INTEGER | Total OCR'd pages |
| processed_status | VARCHAR | waiting/started/finished/errored |
| last_processed_at | TIMESTAMP | Nullable |
| last_process_error | TEXT | Nullable, set on error |
| created_at | TIMESTAMP | Auto-set |

### Chunk
| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| id | UUID | PK |
| document_id | UUID | FK → documents, CASCADE delete |
| content | TEXT | Chunk text |
| page_number | INTEGER | Source page |
| chunk_index | INTEGER | Sequential index |
| chunk_type | VARCHAR | text, title, table (from PP-Structure) |
| bbox | JSONB | [x1,y1,x2,y2] in page coords |
| embedding | Vector(1536) | pgvector column |

### DocumentEnrichment (1:1 with Document)
| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| document_id | UUID | FK, unique |
| title, description | VARCHAR, TEXT | LLM-generated |
| tags | JSON | Array of strings |
| description_embedding, tags_embedding | Vector(1536) | For cue matching |
| enrichment_status | VARCHAR | pending/started/finished/errored |

### Memory (per-chunk context and facts)
| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| document_id, chunk_id | UUID | FK |
| type | VARCHAR | "context" or "fact" |
| content | TEXT | Extracted text |
| embedding | Vector(1536) | For cue matching |

## Chunking Strategy
- **PP-Structure blocks** — 1:1 mapping: each text/title/table block from PaddleOCR PP-Structure becomes one chunk
- Figure/image blocks are excluded from search
- Tables: HTML from PP-Structure → plain text for embedding

## Anti-patterns
- **Don't use L2 distance** — use cosine distance (`<=>`) for text embeddings
- **Don't embed empty strings** — filter before calling OpenAI
- **Don't change embedding dimensions without re-ingesting** — the `Vector(1536)` column and all stored embeddings must match
- **Don't pass embedding as a Python list to SQL** — always use `str(embedding)` for pgvector's text input format
